FORK CONDITIONS

You are permitted to fork this Software. If You publish or Distribute a Fork
or Modified Version, You must comply with all of the following:

a) Attribution. You must clearly and prominently state that Your project is
   derived from the original NTL Software created by David Dev. The author's
   name "David Dev" and a link to the original repository
   (https://github.com/Megamexlevi2) must appear in Your project's README,
   documentation, and any about or credits section of the software itself.

b) Clear derivative marking. Your Fork must not be presented as the original
   NTL project. It must be clearly marked as a fork or derivative in its name,
   description, and all public-facing materials.

c) Name restriction. You may NOT use the name "NTL", "ntl-lang", or any
   confusingly similar name for Your Fork or any project derived from this
   Software. The name "ntl-lang" is the official identifier of this project
   and is reserved exclusively for the Author. Your Fork must use a distinct
   name that does not cause confusion with the original.

d) License retention. You must Distribute Your Fork under this same license
   (NTL Source License v1.0) without adding further restrictions.

e) Change log. You must include a human-readable CHANGES or CHANGELOG file
   describing all modifications made relative to the original Software.

f) Credit preservation. All copyright notices, authorship headers, and
   integrity-guard credits embedded in the Software must remain intact and
   unaltered in Your Fork, including those embedded in binary form.

